.\" Manpage for Simple Shell.
.\" Contact
.TH man 3 "11 Dec 2022" "1.0" "Shimple Shell man page"

.SH NAME
hsh \- explanation ..

.SH SYNOPSIS

Simple Shell program made for holbertonschool.

.SH DESCRIPTION

The simple_shell is a simpler shell based program which is managed from the interface by entering commands,
then said program reads compiles and executes said commands seeing the result in a standard output.

.SH INVOCATION
.br
.\&
.RS
\&> ./hsh

The prompt '(Eshell) $ '
The message ' ' will appear in the terminal.
You can enter commands by following the prompt.
It is not allowed to use multiple commands at the same time, using ';' '&&' '||' specifiers.
To execute the commands enter them and finish by pressing the 'ENTER' key.


.SH EXAMPLES - BUILDING COMMANDS

Here are some commands that can be used in this shell.
.br
.\&
.RS
.TP
.TP

\fb ls [OPTIONS]...\fr  - list directory contents.

.TP
.LP
(Eshell) $ ls
.LP
.TP
.LP
AUTHORS  execmd.c  get_location.c  hsh  main.c  main.h  man_1_simple_shell  README.md
.LP
.TP
.br

\fb echo [SHORT-OPTION]... [STRING]...\fr - display a line of text.

.TP
.LP
(Eshell) $ echo Hello World
.LP
.TP
.LP
Hello World
.LP
.TP

\fBpwd [OPTION]...\fR - print name of current/working directory.

.TP
.br
.LP
(Eshell) $ pwd
.LP
.TP
.LP
/holbertonschool-simple_shell
.LP
.TP
.br

\fBCtrl + D [OPTIONS..]\fR - exit the program.

.TP
.br
.LP
(Eshell) $ ^D
.LP
.TP
.LP
(Eshell) $ Exiting shell....
.LP
.TP
.br

.TP
\fB exit\fR - cause normal process termination.
.TP
.LP
(Eshell) $ exit
.LP
.TP
.LP
exit
.LP

.SH BUILTINS LISTS.C
_

execute.c - list of built-in commands to execute.
-
functions.c - Our own functions.
-
get_location.c - function that takes the command and returns the path.
-
launch.c - launch a program an wait for it to terminate.
-
lines.c - read line of input from stdin divides and tokenizes them.
-
main.c - loop prompt and arguments.
-

.SH RETURN VALUE
.B
If the program succed the return value is 0.
If any problem happens return and error message.

.SH BUGS

Unfortunately - there are no known bugs at this time.

